register.description: PHY register for EMIF1 Access conditions. Read: unrestricted, Write: unrestricted

bitfield.description: Controls the number of DQ samples required for read leveling. The recommended setting for full leveling is 0x3 (128 samples) and for incremental leveling is 0x0 (4 samples).
Selects an algorithm for read leveling. The use of algorithm 1 (set by default) is recommended.
Analysis method of DQ bits during read leveling.

bitenum.description: if the DRAM provides a read response on only one DQ bit. This is the default setting and works with all memory types (memories send responses on all DQ bits or on a single DQ bit).
if the DRAM provides a read response on all DQ bits.

bitfield.description: Selects the status to be observed on the outputs of the DDR PHYs throughCONTROL_EMIF1_SDRAM_CONFIG_EXT_1 register.
ddr3ch1_nreset signal disable. Keep this bit set to 0x1 during normal operations and to 0x0 at boot time and when a memory reset is necessary.

bitenum.description: ddr3ch1_nreset is enabled. It can be asserted by EMIF.
ddr3ch1_nreset is disabled. It is forbidden to EMIF to assert it.

bitfield.description: Control of ODT (on – die termination) settings for the device DDR I/Os. ODT is enabled only during read operations when termination is required.
EMIF_CORE1 clock phase control (shifting by 180°). For normal operation this bit must always be set to 0x0 (disabled).
Enable command PHY 2. 0x1 is the mandatory setting if LPDDR2 is used. When using DDR3 this bit can be set to 0x0 or 0x1. For lower power consumption 0x0 is used.

Enable command PHY 1. 0x1 is the mandatory setting if DDR3 is used. When using LPDDR2 this bit can be set to 0x0 or 0x1. For lower power consumption 0x0 is used. EMIF1_EN_SLICE_0 and EMIF1_EN_SLICE_1 have to be programmed with the same value.

Enable command PHY 0. 0x1 is the mandatory setting if DDR3 is used. When using LPDDR2 this bit can be set to 0x0 or 0x1. For lower power consumption 0x0 is used. EMIF1_EN_SLICE_0 and EMIF1_EN_SLICE_1 have to be programmed with the same value.
